# React & TypeScript Prototype Standards

> **What this file is:** Code standards for all React prototypes and source files in this project. Governs component structure, inline styling rules, state management, data realism, and handoff quality.
>
> **Depends on:** `05-design-system.mdc` — all token values come from there. Never approximate.
> **Triggered by:** Any `.tsx`, `.jsx`, or `.ts` file in the project.

---

## Core Rules

- **Inline styles only.** No external CSS files, no Tailwind, no styled-components, no CSS modules. Every style value must be traceable to a token in `05-design-system.mdc`.
- **No external dependencies** beyond: React, [recharts or chart library], [lucide-react or icon library]. Do not introduce new packages without calling it out.
- **All states included.** Every component must handle: loading (skeleton), error, empty, and success. Never just the happy path.
- **Realistic mock data.** Data must reflect the actual user context from `01-project-context.mdc` — real amounts, real names, real dates. No "Lorem ipsum", no "User Name", no "$0.00" defaults.

---

## Component Structure

### File Organization

```
src/
  components/
    [FeatureName]/
      [FeatureName].tsx       # Main component
      [FeatureName].types.ts  # TypeScript interfaces
      index.ts                # Re-export
  data/
    mockData.ts               # All mock data in one place
  tokens/
    tokens.ts                 # Design system CSS variables as JS constants
  App.tsx
```

### Component Template

```tsx
// ✅ Standard component structure
interface [ComponentName]Props {
  // Explicit types — no `any`
}

const [ComponentName] = ({ prop1, prop2 }: [ComponentName]Props) => {
  const [state, setState] = useState<[Type]>([defaultValue]);

  // Handlers co-located with the state they manage
  const handle[Action] = () => { ... };

  // Derived values calculated inline, not in render
  const derivedValue = useMemo(() => ..., [dep]);

  return (
    <div style={styles.container}>
      {/* JSX */}
    </div>
  );
};

// Styles at bottom of file, grouped by component section
const styles = {
  container: {
    backgroundColor: 'var(--bg-secondary)',
    borderRadius: 'var(--radius-md)',
    padding: 'var(--space-24)',
  } as React.CSSProperties,
};
```

