## Styling Rules

### Always Use CSS Custom Properties

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — traceable to design system tokens
style={{ color: 'var(--text-primary)', padding: 'var(--space-16)' }}

// ❌ WRONG — approximated, untrackable
style={{ color: '#000', padding: '16px' }}
```

### Token Reference Pattern

If you need a JS constant (e.g., for computed values), define tokens in `src/tokens/tokens.ts`:

```ts
// tokens.ts
export const tokens = {
  bgPrimary: 'var(--bg-primary)',
  textPrimary: 'var(--text-primary)',
  spaceMd: 'var(--space-16)',
  radiusMd: 'var(--radius-md)',
  // ... add as needed
} as const;
```

### Typography

```tsx
// ✅ Screen title — Headline Md
style={{ fontSize: '[SIZE]px', lineHeight: '[LINE-HEIGHT]px', fontWeight: [WEIGHT], letterSpacing: '[TRACKING]' }}

// ✅ Body text — Body Lg
style={{ fontSize: '[SIZE]px', lineHeight: '[LINE-HEIGHT]px', fontWeight: 400 }}

// ✅ Button label — Label Lg
style={{ fontSize: '[SIZE]px', lineHeight: '[LINE-HEIGHT]px', fontWeight: [WEIGHT] }}
```

### Touch Targets

All interactive elements must meet minimum touch target size. Use padding to expand small elements:

```tsx
// ✅ Minimum 44x44px touch target
style={{ minWidth: 44, minHeight: 44, display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center' }}
```

